    "## 3. Training the Three Classifiers\n",
    "\n",
    "Phase 1 specified three models: Logistic Regression, Random Forest, and Gradient Boosting.\n",
    "Each one takes a completely different approach to the problem.\n",
    "\n",
    "Logistic Regression learns a set of linear weights for each feature and class combination.\n",
    "It is the simplest of the three and acts as our baseline for what a straightforward approach\n",
    "can achieve.\n",
    "\n",
    "Random Forest builds hundreds of decision trees independently and averages their votes.\n",
    "Each tree sees a random subset of the data and features, which makes the ensemble robust\n",
    "to noise and overfitting.\n",
    "\n",
    "Gradient Boosting also builds decision trees but does it sequentially. Each new tree\n",
    "focuses specifically on the mistakes of the previous ones, which tends to produce\n",
    "higher accuracy at the cost of longer training time.\n",
    "\n",
    "All three models use `class_weight='balanced'` which tells sklearn to automatically\n",
    "upweight rare categories like Legal and downweight dominant ones like Production.\n",
    "This directly compensates for the class imbalance we saw in the data without\n",
    "requiring any resampling."
   ]
  },
