    "## 6. The Career Fit Score System\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the core of the recommendation engine and it directly implements what Phase 1 described.\n",
    "\n",
    "The Career Fit Score for any occupation is computed in two steps. First the classifier predicts\n",
    "which broad career category the user belongs to and gives us a probability score for that\n",
    "category match. Second we compute cosine similarity between the user's feature vector and every\n",
    "occupation in the dataset to find which specific jobs match the user's profile most closely.\n",
    "These two signals are combined into a single score using a weighted average.\n",
    "\n",
    "Why combine both? The classifier captures the high-level personality fit — whether you are\n",
    "fundamentally a technical, social, or creative person. Cosine similarity captures fine-grained\n",
    "occupation-level matching. Together they produce recommendations that are both categorically\n",
    "sensible and numerically precise.\n",
    "\n",
    "Career Fit Score = (0.4 x Category Probability) + (0.6 x Cosine Similarity) x 100"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "1f311522",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-03-31T12:19:51.465199Z",
