    "## Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "What started as a raw dataset of 873 occupations from the O*NET database has been\n",
    "transformed over four phases into a fully functional career recommendation system.\n",
    "\n",
    "Phase 2 cleaned and normalized the data. Phase 3 extracted meaningful features and\n",
    "validated their predictive power. Phase 4 brought it all together with three trained\n",
    "classifiers, a hybrid scoring formula, and an actionable skill gap and learning roadmap\n",
    "system.\n",
    "\n",
    "The most important design decision in this phase was handling class imbalance properly\n",
    "using `class_weight='balanced'` and evaluating with Macro F1 rather than raw accuracy.\n",
    "This ensures the system is genuinely useful for people across all 22 career categories,\n",
    "not just the ones that happen to have the most data points.\n",
    "\n",
    "The Career Fit Score formula combines two signals that complement each other: the\n",
    "classifier's domain-level prediction and cosine similarity's occupation-level precision.\n",
    "The result is a recommendation that is both categorically sensible and numerically\n",
    "grounded in the user's actual feature profile.\n",
    "\n",
    "The system is fully modular. Changing the user profile dictionary and re-running\n",
    "produces a completely new personalized recommendation report in seconds."
